 St John 's College and a 74-year-old businessman have been locked in a battle over an unkempt hedgerow between their properties in Warwickshire .
The dispute began when Anthony Bethell decided he would pay for work to restore the ancient 180-yard hedge , marks the boundary between his home and college 's land .
But he claims St Johns has refused to agree with him and he has been forced to take the college to court .